author: Inside Edition
description: A pilot made an emergency landing off the beach in Oak Island, North Carolina. First responders on a jetski and a surfboard made it to the stricken plane. Rescuers pulled the pilot feet first out of the flooded cockpit. They got the pilot onto a rescue sled attached to the jetski and brought him to shore to waiting paramedics. Inside Edition's Les Trent spoke to pilot Mark Finkelstein and firefighters Chad Butchello, Chris Dunham and Austin Lancaster.
title: First Responders Rescue Plane Pilot Stuck at Sea

author: Inside Edition
description: John Rudat, 20, is recovering from a knife attack after he came to the aid of a group of young women who were being harassed on a tram in the German city of Dresden. The part-time model who lives in New York, was hospitalized with knife wounds to his face after intervening. Rudat spent two days in the hospital and has no regrets. "I'm proud for what I did and what I stood up against," Rudat says. "To be honest, I think my modeling career was very short-lived."
title: Man Recovers From Knife Attack After Aiding Woman Being Harassed

author: Inside Edition
description: When Elle Woods moved her dog in with her at Harvard Law in the 2001 movie "Legally Blonde," she may have been on to something. Nearly 25 years later, it seems other colleges are coming up with pet policies for their campus residences. Molly Cheer attends the University of Northern Colorado and dorms with her cat, Louie. She says Louie brings her a lot of comfort while trying to get through these tough years at school. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: More Colleges Allowing Pets to Live in Dorms

author: Inside Edition
description: Travis Decker, was questioned by police after he was involved in a fender bender. Seventy-two hours later, Decker allegedly murdered his children Paityn, Evelyn, and Olivia at a campsite in Washington State's Wenatchee National Forest.
title: Manhunt for Murder Suspect Travis Decker Continues #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Ava Cooper was born with multiple heart defects and endured many open-heart surgeries. Last year, when Ava was 10, she went into heart failure. A heart transplant became her best option, and the waiting began for a donor. After 215 days, she learned she was getting a heart. Inside Edition spoke to Ava and her parents, Sean and Jaime. The next day, Ava successfully underwent the 14-hour transplant surgery.
title: 11-Year-Old Girl Gets New Heart After 215 Days in Hospital

author: Inside Edition
description: At 90-years-old, one might start to consider slowing down a little, but not Sister Celine Goessl. She says she's exactly where she belongs: at the Wisconsin food pantry founded by her order, the Sisters of Mercy of the Holy Cross, back in 1983. She's been running the place for the past five years and tells WSAW that she's only seen the need for her services grow. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 90-Year-Old Nun Still Runs Food Pantry Founded in 1983

author: Inside Edition
description: Bruce Willis' wife, Emma Heming Willis, is opening up about the moment she noticed a change in her husband.
title: What Was the First Symptom of Dementia for Bruce Willis? #shorts
